Timeshift Series 14 Episode 1 of 7

A trip back to the days when 'style wars' were just that - violent
confrontations about the clothes you wore. Spring 2014 marks the
50th anniversary of the bank holiday 'battles of the beaches', when
hundreds of mods and rockers flocked to seaside resorts on scooters
and motorbikes in search of thrills and spills.

Timeshift tells the story of how this led to violence, arrests and
widespread concern about the state of British youth. But mods and
rockers had more in common than was first obvious; they were the
first generation of baby boomers to reach their teenage years at a
time when greater prosperity and wider freedoms were transforming
what it meant to be young.
